{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0547cee0-c21d-4d6d-bbb5-e497f82ef041","content":"The template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation: `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `preferNameDirectory` — typically `true` for project templates\n- `defaultName` — fallback name when user doesn't supply one (e.g., `\"WebApi1\"`)\n\n**Functional issues:**\n- The `Framework` symbol is defined but never wired to anything (no `replaces` to substitute into the `.csproj` `<TargetFramework>` element). Without that, choosing a framework at `dotnet new` time has no effect.\n\n**Packaging consideration:**\n- You'll need a `.csproj` or `.nuspec` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>` and content referencing this folder to produce the NuGet package — make sure that exists alongside this config.\n\n**What looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, and `tags` are all properly set.\n\nIn short: fix the `Framework` symbol so it actually replaces the target framework in the project file, add the `$schema` reference, and confirm you have a packaging project — then it's ready.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc38ff76-58a0-4fbe-bc70-627760c58415","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"93D7:D37CE:DEDDA77:F51A410:69F2A8DB"},"id":"ebd5ca41-6d9b-4dfd-b648-605558433878","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:57:08.696Z","parentId":"e1bb342c-24e5-455c-a4a3-20ac3a96ca80"}
